==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[back]]-[[formation]]}}

# {{linguistics}} The process by which a new word is formed by removing part of an older word that is falsely perceived to be a ''[[bound morpheme]]'' attached to a ''[[root morpheme]]''.
#: ''example:'' the word ''[[editor]]'' was incorrectly thought to be from the [[root]] ''[[edit]]'' and the [[suffix]] ''[[-or]]'', where it is actually a single [[morpheme]].

